    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "What we're doing is subtlely wrong, but it has never been correct.\r\nWe're waiting _inside the gossip validation_ for the slot to arrive. This may result in the gossiped block being eventually propagated. The outcome is the same with or without the added clock disparity allowance.\r\n\r\nThe validation rule instead says to immediately IGNORE.\r\nLikely the right solution involves comparing block.slot against `getSlotsSinceGenesis(genesisTime - MAX_GOSSIP_CLOCK_DISPARITY)`.\r\neg:\r\n```typescript\r\nif (block.message.slot > getSlotsSinceGenesis(config, genesisTime - MAX_GOSSIP_CLOCK_DISPARITY)) {\r\n  logger.warn(\"block from the future\", ...);\r\n  chain.receiveBlock(block);\r\n  throw new GossipError(IGNORE);\r\n}\r\n```",
